main event: A civilian in Memphis, Tennessee reported seeing a golden object traveling at excessive speed at an estimated altitude of 10,000-20,000 feet, traveling from north to south for approximately one minute. The observer was a ground-visual witness and there were no photographs taken.
interesting points: The sighting took place in Memphis, Tennessee, and was reported by a civilian observer.
The object was described as golden and was traveling at an 'excessive speed', although the actual speed is not specified in the report.
The estimated altitude of the object was between 10,000-20,000 feet, and it was the only aircraft reported over Memphis at the time of the sighting.
The observer mentioned that the object traveled from north to south for around one minute, suggesting a relatively short duration of the sighting.
The observer's description of the object's altitude, speed, and direction of travel indicate an anomalous nature of the sighting.
sighted object: Golden object traveling at excessive speed
